<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6822116>
    dc:description "FIG. 4. Morphological comparisons of the frontal sacs and noseleaves in A — Macronycteris commersonii (FMNH 213588, ♀), Madagascar, Province d’Antsiranana, Réserve Spéciale d’Ankarana [now Parc National], near Andrafiabe Cave, 31 October 2010; B — M. gigas (FMNH 128212, ♀), Senegal, Casmance, Diabane, 12 km SW of Adeane, 15 January 1983; C — M. vittatus (FMNH 192800, ♀, sequenced for Cyt-b), Tanzania, Pemba Island, Kaskazini Region, Micheweni District, Kilijini Village, 3 August 2006; and D — Doryrhina cyclops (FMNH 164973), Uganda, Masindi District, Budongo Forest, 25 June 1998. The form of M. cryptovalorona is similar to M. commersonii and no comparative specimen material was available for M. thomensis. Drawing by Velizar Simeonovski" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6822116/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

